commit_list.message: Se agregaron algunas páginas, se desactivo el jquery del banner y se cambió el css
js code linked to css and html
First commit: working in console mode
Removed letter.js and word.js because this app does not require those files.
giphy api url was updated to https in order to avoid problems with heroku
css lines below h1 and h2 added
css updated and character initial values corrected

Merge pull request #2 from Ronman73/master

added new file

Merge pull request #1 from CoreyDH/master

add some files
selection of word and creation of event listener
Now users will have a wins counter and losses counter. Additionally, the height of the chat was set to a minimum height in case the chat is empty.
changed textarea to div and synchronized turns with db
Now users will show when they get disconnected in the chat
bevo.gif was changed for bevo.jpg because of an incompability problem with heroku

Links prev and next were added to the head in order to indicate that the first content is the index. The size of the the social links in the footer was increased for better user experience on mobile devices
fixed bad submit of the project to git

Merge branch 'master' of github.com:KevinAngeles/my-web

Conflicts:
	css/index.css
	index.html
Social icons were added to the footer
Css was updated in order to work with bootstrap 3
Fixed typo error in back-end description
Title was added to github hyperlink on index
Typo error back-end info index html
Added spanish flag for language selection in index
resize of footer and header content was fixed in with css
First commit - Only index was created
listener added and files structure updated
Once an article is saved the button will be disabled
Now users can delete articles and the package.json was updated
Correction of git url of the project in README.md
added panels and borders to the html
Added post api to store the articles
Added Readme and License, Removed Port from server.js
added mongoose, created controllers and models, and moved the listener from server.js to bin/www
Deleted unnecessary comments below saved news
Updated date formatting on saved news
Added validation of dates and topic
Fixed typo. If there is an error, requests won't be made to NYT api
Now when an article is saved it will be placed on top of the previous saved articles instead of the bottom
Solved empty results. Now it shows a message

Results were updated with new NYT api key (Snippet). Bundle generated by webpack was deleted because a postinstallation script was included in package.json. The postinstallation script will automatically generate the bundle.js after running npm install.
screenshots were removed from the project
corrected name of pictures of rovers in roverinfo.html (at code.js)
an slidershow was added to roverimages.html
the initial and max dates will be updated on the calendar depending on which rover is selected
moved background of the day from code.js to a new file
roverinfo had some broken html code that was corrected
html corrected, asteroids js corrected the declaration of variables, moved asteroid style to an external css
removed link from NASA from nav
Partially solved the bug at the rovers form. Now it is working only there is data and only if the dates are in the correct format.
Screenshots were removed because those screens won't be used in the project
linked the date with they query
a radio button was added to the initial form. Clicking on a radio button will disable an earth input
Added selection of rovers and cameras with some basic ajax
css modified (line below h1 and h2)
added a gitignore file to ignore .DS_Store OS X generated files
get zip codes from server and added a modal in the client to show zip codes
fixed insert file, reorganized project and merged form with map
Removed timestamps creation. The file that reads the csv data will now use config values directly from config.json and will insert it into the database
Added a module with helper methods to handle errors and refresh access_token.
Now, users can download their own playlists by just clicking a button. Fixes #5
Now, display_name will be used as a file name, unless it has an invalid value (non-empty ), in such a case the Spotify user id will be used. Fixes #4
An offset was added to the playlist request to retrieve more than 100 tracks. Fixes #1
Now, users can download playlists from other Spotify accounts. Fixes #2
First commit. Application can retrieve .xlsx file with a list of playlists and tracks from an Spotify account.
Now, there is a method to refresh the access token before it expires. Fixes #3
fixed bootstrap small column in the form
Now, users can select between their own accounts and other accounts. Also added react, reactstrap, Gulp, and webpack.
Added a logout link for users
